00:05:16.220 --> 00:05:19.290
And Google Play
services obviously

00:05:19.290 --> 00:05:23.130
has an API to integrate
with these variable devices.

00:05:23.130 --> 00:05:26.270
Because you need to transfer
things between these devices

00:05:26.270 --> 00:05:28.020
and communicate across them.

00:05:28.020 --> 00:05:30.420
And there are three APIs
that we are launching

00:05:30.420 --> 00:05:34.970
as part of Google Play services
in the Android Wear data API.

00:05:34.970 --> 00:05:37.800
The first part is
the message API.

00:05:37.800 --> 00:05:42.600
The message API allows you to
send uni-directional messages

00:05:42.600 --> 00:05:45.970
between the wearable and
the phone, or tablet.

00:05:45.970 --> 00:05:48.490
Or the phone tablet
to the wearable.

00:05:48.490 --> 00:05:50.080
These can be control signals.

00:05:50.080 --> 00:05:52.290
For example, you can
tell the wearable

00:05:52.290 --> 00:05:56.030
to change the media track that
is playing on your Android

00:05:56.030 --> 00:05:56.930
phone.

00:05:56.930 --> 00:06:01.000
Or you can have your Android
phone instruct the wearable

00:06:01.000 --> 00:06:04.060
to launch an intent that
gets visible to the user.

00:06:04.060 --> 00:06:06.560
So that's a great API
to share information

00:06:06.560 --> 00:06:09.560
between the device you
have in the pocket,

00:06:09.560 --> 00:06:10.770
and the wearable device.

00:06:10.770 --> 00:06:14.360
The second API is the asset API.

00:06:14.360 --> 00:06:17.640
The asset API is
used to transfer

00:06:17.640 --> 00:06:20.370
binary blobs--
images, for example,

00:06:20.370 --> 00:06:23.640
or other kinds of binary
data-- between the wearable

00:06:23.640 --> 00:06:25.130
and the other device.

00:06:25.130 --> 00:06:27.100
So this can, for
example, be an image.

00:06:27.100 --> 00:06:30.010
One use case would be
your phone downloads

00:06:30.010 --> 00:06:31.680
an image to the phone, right?

00:06:31.680 --> 00:06:34.520
It resizes it to
match the resolution

00:06:34.520 --> 00:06:35.790
of the wearable device.

00:06:35.790 --> 00:06:39.860
And it then sends it over to
the wearable device as an asset.

00:06:39.860 --> 00:06:44.210
That's a perfect example of data
being transferred as an asset.

00:06:44.210 --> 00:06:46.360
Then we have DataItem.

00:06:46.360 --> 00:06:52.570
DataItem is a message
exchange in this API

00:06:52.570 --> 00:06:55.010
